# Git LFS — large model artifacts (trained weights).
# See ../.agents/knowledge/devops.md → "Version control & model artifacts".
#
# ⚠️ INERT until you stop gitignoring these patterns. Right now `.gitignore`
# contains `*.pt`, so git ignores weights entirely and LFS never sees them.
#
# To START versioning weights via LFS (non-destructive, no history rewrite —
# nothing is tracked yet):
#   1) git lfs install                       # once per machine
#   2) edit .gitignore: remove the `*.pt` line (keep dataset/, *.zip ignored)
#   3) git add .gitattributes yolo26n.pt yolo26s.pt <your-best>.pt
#   4) git commit -m "chore: track model weights via Git LFS"
#
# Datasets and *.zip stay OUT of git/LFS (too large for GitHub LFS free tier).
# Keep them reproducible via download_dataset.py, or use DVC with an external
# remote (Google Drive / S3). See devops.md for the tradeoff.

*.pt      filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.pth     filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.onnx    filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.engine  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.tflite  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
